He won the Shinto Religious Studies Prize in {{ill|1984|ja|1984th year|12=draft|12=draft}} for his work on the formation of the {{ill|Urabe clan|ja|卜部氏|12=draft|12=draft}}. In {{ill|1991|ja|1991st year|12=draft|12=draft}}, he became a researcher at the {{ill|Okura Institute for Spiritual Culture|ja|大倉精神文化研究所|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref>'Contemporary Japanese Biographical Directory' (2002)</ref>. He earned his doctorate in {{ill|1995|ja|1995th year|12=draft|12=draft}} for his thesis on {{ill|The State and Rituals of the Heian Period|ja|平安時代の国家と祭祀|12=draft|12=draft}}.
