'''Okada Chuangji''' (岡田莊司) was a Japanese historian of Shinto
{{BLP sources|date=July 8, 2016}} '''Shōji Okada''' (岡田 莊司, born {{ill|November 22, 1948|ja|1948th year 11月22日|12=draft|12=draft}}) is a Japanese {{ill|Shinto scholar|ja|神道学者|12=draft|12=draft}}. He holds a {{ill|Doctorate in History|ja|博士（歴史学）|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|1995|ja|1995th year|12=draft|12=draft}}) and is an emeritus professor at the {{ill|Faculty of Shinto Studies, Kokugakuin University|ja|國學院大學神道文化学部|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref name=名誉教授>[http://pr.kokugakuin.ac.jp/event/2019/06/05/130737/ June 5, 2019, Conferment Ceremony of the Title of Professor Emeritus] Accessed February 2022.</ref>.
== Biography == Born in {{ill|Yukinoshita|ja|雪ノ下|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kamakura City|ja|鎌倉市|12=draft|12=draft}}. He graduated in {{ill|1971|ja|1971st year|12=draft|12=draft}} from the {{ill|Department of History, Faculty of Letters, Kokugakuin University|ja|國學院大学文学部史学科|12=draft|12=draft}} and completed his master’s degree at the {{ill|Graduate School of Letters, Kokugakuin University|ja|國學院大学大学院文学研究科|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|1973|ja|1973rd year|12=draft|12=draft}}. In {{ill|1981|ja|1981st year|12=draft|12=draft}}, he became a lecturer at Kokugakuin University, an associate professor in {{ill|1984|ja|1984th year|12=draft|12=draft}}, and a full professor in {{ill|1992|ja|1992nd year|12=draft|12=draft}}. He retired in {{ill|2019|ja|2019th year|12=draft|12=draft}}, receiving the title of professor emeritus<ref name=名誉教授/>.
He won the Shinto Religious Studies Prize in {{ill|1984|ja|1984th year|12=draft|12=draft}} for his work on the formation of the {{ill|Urabe clan|ja|卜部氏|12=draft|12=draft}}. In {{ill|1991|ja|1991st year|12=draft|12=draft}}, he became a researcher at the {{ill|Okura Institute for Spiritual Culture|ja|大倉精神文化研究所|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref>'Contemporary Japanese Biographical Directory' (2002)</ref>. He earned his doctorate in {{ill|1995|ja|1995th year|12=draft|12=draft}} for his thesis on {{ill|The State and Rituals of the Heian Period|ja|平安時代の国家と祭祀|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Publications == * *The Daijōsai Ceremony* (大嘗の祭り), {{ill|Gakuseisha|ja|学生社|12=draft|12=draft}}, 1990 * *The State and Rituals of the Heian Period* (平安時代の国家と祭祀), {{ill|Zoku Gunsho Ruijū Kansei-kai|ja|続群書類従完成会|12=draft|12=draft}}, 1996 * *The Daijōsai and Ancient Rituals* (大嘗祭と古代の祭祀), {{ill|Yoshikawa Kōbunkan|ja|吉川弘文館|12=draft|12=draft}}, 2019 ISBN 9784642083508 * *Ancient Japanese Emperors and the Ritual System* (古代天皇と神祇の祭祀体系), Yoshikawa Kōbunkan, 2022 ISBN 9784642046688 * *Medieval Shinto and the Faith System of Shrines* (中世神道と神社の信仰体系), Yoshikawa Kōbunkan, 2024 ISBN 9784642029933
=== Co-Authored and Edited Works === * *How to Read Norioto and Ōharae Kotoba for Modern People* (現代人のための祝詞 大祓詞の読み方), 1st rev. ed., co-supervised by {{ill|Zemaru Sakamoto|ja|阪本是丸|12=draft|12=draft}}, co-edited by {{ill|Toshishi Ōshima|ja|大島敏史|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yukihiro Nakamura|ja|中村幸弘|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Uibun Shoin|ja|右文書院|12=draft|12=draft}}, 2000 * *Studies on the Shrine and Kami Rank System in Ancient Provinces* (古代諸国神社神階制の研究), edited by {{ill|Iwata Shoin|ja|岩田書院|12=draft|12=draft}}, 2002 * *Rituals and Halls of the Ancient Izumo Taisha Shrine* (古代出雲大社の祭儀と神殿), co-authored with {{ill|Hayatsugu Sugiyama|ja|椙山林継|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Hitoshi Mure|ja|牟禮仁|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Tsuyoshi Nishikida|ja|錦田剛志|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Mitsuaki Matsuo|ja|松尾充晶|12=draft|12=draft}}, Gakuseisha, 2005 * *Shinto and Japanese Culture* (神道と日本文化), co-authored by {{ill|Masahiko Asoyani|ja|安蘇谷正彦|12=draft|12=draft}}, Hayatsugu Sugiyama, {{ill|Masayuki Nakanishi|ja|中西正幸|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sakae Mogi|ja|茂木栄|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sadazumi Mogi|ja|茂木貞純|12=draft|12=draft}}, Hyōgo Prefecture Shrine Association, {{ill|Eibunkō Shō Publishing|ja|戎光祥出版|12=draft|12=draft}}, 2006 * *A Dictionary of Shrines' Histories and Festivals* (事典神社の歴史と祭り), co-edited with {{ill|Mamorue Sasaō|ja|笹生衛|12=draft|12=draft}}, Yoshikawa Kōbunkan, 2013 ISBN 9784642080859
