== Biography == Born in {{ill|Yukinoshita|ja|雪ノ下|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kamakura City|ja|鎌倉市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He graduated in {{ill|1971|ja|1971st year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} from the {{ill|Department of History, Faculty of Letters, Kokugakuin University|ja|國學院大学文学部史学科|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and completed his master’s degree at the {{ill|Graduate School of Letters, Kokugakuin University|ja|國學院大学大学院文学研究科|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|1973|ja|1973rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In {{ill|1981|ja|1981st year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, he became a lecturer at Kokugakuin University, an associate professor in {{ill|1984|ja|1984th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and a full professor in {{ill|1992|ja|1992nd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He retired in {{ill|2019|ja|2019th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, receiving the title of professor emeritus<ref name=名誉教授/>.
He won the Shinto Religious Studies Prize in {{ill|1984|ja|1984th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} for his work on the formation of the {{ill|Urabe clan|ja|卜部氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In {{ill|1991|ja|1991st year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, he became a researcher at the {{ill|Okura Institute for Spiritual Culture|ja|大倉精神文化研究所|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref>'Contemporary Japanese Biographical Directory' (2002)</ref>. He earned his doctorate in {{ill|1995|ja|1995th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} for his thesis on {{ill|The State and Rituals of the Heian Period|ja|平安時代の国家と祭祀|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Publications == * *The Daijōsai Ceremony* (大嘗の祭り), {{ill|Gakuseisha|ja|学生社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, 1990 * *The State and Rituals of the Heian Period* (平安時代の国家と祭祀), {{ill|Zoku Gunsho Ruijū Kansei-kai|ja|続群書類従完成会|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, 1996 * *The Daijōsai and Ancient Rituals* (大嘗祭と古代の祭祀), {{ill|Yoshikawa Kōbunkan|ja|吉川弘文館|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, 2019 ISBN 9784642083508 * *Ancient Japanese Emperors and the Ritual System* (古代天皇と神祇の祭祀体系), Yoshikawa Kōbunkan, 2022 ISBN 9784642046688 * *Medieval Shinto and the Faith System of Shrines* (中世神道と神社の信仰体系), Yoshikawa Kōbunkan, 2024 ISBN 9784642029933
=== Co-Authored and Edited Works === * *How to Read Norioto and Ōharae Kotoba for Modern People* (現代人のための祝詞 大祓詞の読み方), 1st rev. ed., co-supervised by {{ill|Zemaru Sakamoto|ja|阪本是丸|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, co-edited by {{ill|Toshishi Ōshima|ja|大島敏史|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Yukihiro Nakamura|ja|中村幸弘|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Uibun Shoin|ja|右文書院|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, 2000 * *Studies on the Shrine and Kami Rank System in Ancient Provinces* (古代諸国神社神階制の研究), edited by {{ill|Iwata Shoin|ja|岩田書院|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, 2002 * *Rituals and Halls of the Ancient Izumo Taisha Shrine* (古代出雲大社の祭儀と神殿), co-authored with {{ill|Hayatsugu Sugiyama|ja|椙山林継|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Hitoshi Mure|ja|牟禮仁|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tsuyoshi Nishikida|ja|錦田剛志|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Mitsuaki Matsuo|ja|松尾充晶|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Gakuseisha, 2005 * *Shinto and Japanese Culture* (神道と日本文化), co-authored by {{ill|Masahiko Asoyani|ja|安蘇谷正彦|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Hayatsugu Sugiyama, {{ill|Masayuki Nakanishi|ja|中西正幸|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Sakae Mogi|ja|茂木栄|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Sadazumi Mogi|ja|茂木貞純|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Hyōgo Prefecture Shrine Association, {{ill|Eibunkō Shō Publishing|ja|戎光祥出版|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, 2006 * *A Dictionary of Shrines' Histories and Festivals* (事典神社の歴史と祭り), co-edited with {{ill|Mamorue Sasaō|ja|笹生衛|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Yoshikawa Kōbunkan, 2013 ISBN 9784642080859
=== Annotations === * *Shinto Taikei, Shrine Edition 20: Tsurugaoka* (神道大系 神社編 20 鶴岡), co-annotated with {{ill|Takeshi Toyohara|ja|豊原武|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Shinto Taikei Compilation Committee, 1979 * *Shinto Taikei, Classical Annotation Edition 8: Nakatomi Harai* (神道大系 古典註釈編 8 中臣祓註釈), annotated, Shinto Taikei Compilation Committee, 1985 * *Shinto Taikei, Essay Edition 9: Urabe Shinto (Lower)* (神道大系 論説編 9 吉田神道 下), annotated, Shinto Taikei Compilation Committee, 1991
